        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 10 at 10:44PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 1044 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms across eastern Carter County, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail. Frequent
lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ridgeway, Alzada, Belltower, Capitol, Albion and Mill Iron.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
